<testset xmlns="http://cpee.org/ns/properties/2.0">
  <executionhandler>ruby</executionhandler>
  <dataelements>
    <llm_answer>{"response":"The lamp lumen has been adjusted to 30 to bring the light level into the target range of 200-300 lux for the evening (approximately 227 lux based on the provided formula). The event has been logged."}</llm_answer>
    <sensor_payload>{"dataset_timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:00:00","actual_timestamp":"2026-06-05T10:25:11.658430","trigger":"scheduled_30m","ambient_light_lux":543,"occupancy_count":1,"motion_detected":true,"hour":10.0,"current_light_lumen":0,"gt_target_lumen":"0-0","gt_target_lumen_min":0,"gt_target_lumen_max":0}</sensor_payload>
    <time>midday</time>
    <llm_input>Do not request from the sensors again. It is currently midday, the lamp is currently at 0 and the current lux is at 543. Do not change the lumen of the lamp unless any of the following rules hold: (1) If it is morning aim for 100-200 lux, (2) If it is midday aim for 300-500 lux, (3) If it is afternoon aim for 200-300 lux, and (4) If it is evening aim for 200-300 lux! Use the logging tool! Use the following lumen to lux formula: lumen*7.5761. Only send rounded to integer lumen.</llm_input>
    <lumen>751</lumen>
    <occupancy>1</occupancy>
    <current>0</current>
    <ambient>543</ambient>
    <motion>true</motion>
